definition: Sydney, capital of New South Wales, Australia (Tw)
snow/snowfall/CL:場|场[chang2]/to have the appearance of snow/to wipe away, off or out/to clean

sentences.english: This color composite view was recorded under dark skies near Sydney, Australia.
sentences.chinese: 这张彩色合成影像是在澳洲的雪梨附近所拍摄。

sentences.english: It’s so nice to be able to come “down under’’ to Sydney, thanks to your kind invitation.
sentences.chinese: 你好意邀请，才使我们能够“南下”雪梨。

sentences.english: My favorite fruit is to Sydney, he is a common fruit in autumn.
sentences.chinese: 我最喜欢的水果是雪梨，他是秋天一种常见的水果。

sentences.english: Ribb was born at Sydney in Australia.
sentences.chinese: 瑞柏出生于澳洲的雪梨。

sentences.english: Sydney Harbor Bridge in Australia and the Skytower in New Zealand are both flooded with people.
sentences.chinese: 澳洲的雪梨大桥及纽西兰的天空之塔都会涌入许多人。

sentences.english: Arrange it on top of the celeriac cake. Cover with sherry sauce.
sentences.chinese: 把切开的鸡肉放在西芹根蛋糕上，浇上雪梨酒酱汁。

sentences.english: On our last visit I didn't find any particularly well-priced yarns.
sentences.chinese: 上次来雪梨时觉得毛线没有特别优惠。

sentences.english: I plan to buy some herb Chuan Bei tomorrow to put together with sugar.
sentences.chinese: 明天我打算买点川贝，自制冰糖川贝炖雪梨。
